'''金门'''指的是在金门坝山谷两侧的砂岩悬崖。1875年，名叫J.N.R.范·雷南的农民和其妻子在去往乌尔兰德的新农庄时在此停留。当他看见最后一道落日余晖落在悬崖上时，就将这里命名为“金门”。<ref name=Ribbok>{{cite web| last =Footprint| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Rhebok Hiking Trail| work =| publisher =| date =| url =http://www.footprint.co.za/Ribbokdescription2.pdf| format =| doi =| accessdate =2006-08-13| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070928173225/http://www.footprint.co.za/Ribbokdescription2.pdf| archivedate =2007-09-28}}</ref>

 

1963年，为保护该区美丽的自然景观，47.92km²的土地被宣告成为国家公园。1981年，公园扩大到62.41km²（15,420英亩），1988年再度发展为116.33km²（28,746英亩）。<ref name=Ribbok/>2004年，公园与毗邻的库瓦国家公园相连。<ref name=government>{{cite web| last =South African Government Information| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =QwaQwa National Park Incorporated With The Golden Gate Highlands National Park| work =| publisher =| date =| url =http://www.info.gov.za/speeches/2004/04031813461001.htm| doi =| accessdate =2006-08-13| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070930165351/http://www.info.gov.za/speeches/2004/04031813461001.htm| archivedate =2007-09-30}}</ref> 2007年，完成了库瓦国家公园的合并，公园面积增至340km²（84,016英亩）。<ref name=Jacana/><ref name=annual>{{cite web

